race.comment: THE VOCALIST (3) is racing well without winning this time in and looks to have found a very suitable race here that lacks depth. He tried hard for second here in a BM66 two starts back before a close up fourth at Pakenham and either of those runs go a long way to winning this. MASH AND GRAVY (11) struggled up to a BM66 last time having won two easier races prior. This suits better and he'll carry just 52kg after the claim. Expecting a much better performance this time around. PATSY'S STAR (2) was poor last time but had been coming along okay prior and might be looking for this trip now. REDWOOD SHADOW (6) has minor claims on best form.
